A cutlass is a type of sword, similar to a sabre, and is has a curved blade. The blade is often flared towards the end of the sword, and the sword is often fitted with a hand guard which could also serve the purpose of being an armoured fist in a close quarter battle.

They are often attributed as being the weapon of choice for seventeenth century pirates and is known by many names - hanger, short sabre or cuttoe by infantrymen, or the more popular cutlass by pirates.